            <bio>
               <p>Martin East is a senior lecturer in the Faculty of Education of The University of Auckland. He has a specific interest in researching language assessment issues, in particular modifications to traditional testing practices designed to enhance test takers' interaction with the test and to encourage positive impact on the test takers.</p>
               <p>Chris King has been teaching English as an additional language, in New Zealand and overseas, for over ten years. He is a lecturer in the Department of Language Studies at Unitec New Zealand, and is currently teaching on an intermediate-level course. He has a broad range of research interests, including both computer-assisted and task-based language teaching, and learner autonomy.</p>
